title: Millburn High School girls tennis team wins third straight Tournament of Champions crown
text:
Millburn High School girls tennis team wins third straight Tournament of Champions crown October 21, 2015 Last updated: Wednesday, October 21, 2015, 4:00 PM By Jim Connelly Buy this photo staff photo by jim connelly 
The Millburn High School varsity girls tennis team won the first three points of the match this afternoon against Holmdel High School at the Garden State Tennis Center in Edison to assure itself of a third consecutive New Jersey State Interscholastic Athletic Association Tournament of Champions crown. 
Stephanie Schrage staked Millburn to a 1-0 lead with a 6-1, 6-1 defeat of Brianna Gibbs at first singles. 
The second doubles team of Elizabeth Gray and Anna Mandel made the score 2-0 with a 6-4, 7-5 defeat of Jaimee Ratkowski and Natalie Cipriano. 
The first doubles team of Isabella Waung and Sydney Zirlin clinched the Millers' eighth T of C crown, tied with Newark Academy for the most titles in tournament history, with a 6-4, 7-6 (7-5) defeat of Emily Kong and Victoria Vought. 
See the Thursday, Oct. 29, 2015, print edition of The Item of Millburn and Short Hills for more details.
